comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-03-31T22:15:11.346Z",codex-agent,TOON output currently wraps item metadata under front_matter and should emit root-level fields.
  "2026-03-31T22:16:50.485Z",codex-agent,"Implemented codec changes in item-format: TOON serializer now writes root-level fields plus body, parser accepts both new root-object shape and legacy wrapped front_matter shape for backward compatibility; updated validation tests and docs to reflect unwrapped TOON item format."
  "2026-03-31T22:22:47.310Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/item-format-validation.spec.ts tests/unit/item-format-migration.spec.ts tests/unit/item-store.spec.ts passed (40/40); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 57/57 files and 578/578 tests plus 100% statements/branches/functions/lines. Migration verification: config set item-format json_markdown then toon scanned and migrated 239 items each pass, and rg '^front_matter:' .agents/pm returned zero matches so all item .toon files now start with root fields (for example id:)."
  "2026-03-31T22:24:14.558Z",codex-agent,"pm test pm-h3tp --run --timeout 7200 passed all 3 linked commands: full coverage gate and both targeted TOON codec regressions."
